Transcription Factor Analysis for ATF3 Promoter

Analysis Summary

This report presents the analysis of the ATF3 promoter sequence for potential transcription factor binding sites. The analysis identified binding motifs for various transcription factors and their distribution along the sequence.

Length of analyzed sequence: 57,944 nucleotides

Overview of Transcription Factor Binding Sites

Transcription Factor Binding Sites Count Description
ETS 1268 ETS family factors play key roles in cell differentiation, cell cycle control, and cell migration
IRF 381 Interferon regulatory factors involved in immune response and cell cycle regulation
E-box 291 Binding sites for bHLH transcription factors, important for tissue-specific gene expression
NFAT 241 Nuclear factor of activated T-cells, involved in immune response
CAAT-box 190 Promoter element important for RNA polymerase binding and transcription initiation
TATA-box 146 Core promoter element required for accurate transcription initiation
GC-box 54 Promoter element often found in housekeeping genes, binds SP1
SP1 27 Specificity Protein 1, constitutively expressed transcription factor
CREB 22 cAMP response element-binding protein, regulates transcription in response to cAMP levels
STAT 17 Signal Transducer and Activator of Transcription, activated by cytokines and growth factors
AP-1 12 Activator Protein 1, regulates gene expression in response to various stimuli
CRE 2 cAMP Response Element, regulates expression in response to cAMP levels
NF-kB 0 Nuclear Factor kappa B, involved in immune and inflammatory responses
HRE 0 Hormone Response Element, mediates transcriptional responses to hormones
GATA 0 GATA binding proteins, important for development and differentiation
